'''Enayatollah Reza''' ({{lang-fa|عنایت‌الله رضا}}; June 18, 1920 in [[Rasht]] – July 20, 2010 in [[Tehran]])<ref>{{cite news |title=مراسم يادبود درگذشت عنايت الله رضا برگزارشد |url=http://www.radiofarda.com/archive/news/20100714/143/143.html?id=2099098 |work=[[Radio Farda]] |date=14 July 2010 |accessdate=3 September 2010 }}</ref> was an Iranian historian and professor of philosophy, a former member of the Iranian [[Communist Party]], and a former Iranian military officer.<ref>{{citation|title=Islamism and modernism: the changing discourse in Iran|volume=24|series=Modern Middle East series|first=Farhang|last=Rajaee|publisher=University of Texas Press|year=2007|isbn=978-0-292-71756-5|page=48}}</ref> He was a member of the Supreme Academic Council of the Centre for Iranian and Islamic Studies in [[Tehran]], [[Iran]], the publishers of the ''[[Encyclopaedia Islamica]]''.<ref>[http://www.brill.nl/brochures/Isla-preview.pdf Preview] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101102171219/http://brill.nl/brochures/Isla-preview.pdf |date=2010-11-02 }} of ''[[Encyclopaedia Islamica]]'', [[Brill Publishers]]. Retrieved 2010-02-28.</ref> His research concerned the historical regions of [[Azerbaijan (Iran)|Iranian Azerbaijan]] and [[Arran (Caucasus)|Caucasian Arran]]; based on this research, he claimed that "Azerbaijan" should properly refer only to the land south of the [[Aras River]] (in Iran) and that the [[Azerbaijan|country of Azerbaijan]] should instead be called "Aran".<ref>[http://www.iranchamber.com/geography/articles/arran_real_azerbaijan.php "Arran, the real name of Adjerbadjan"], Interview with Reza, Iran Chamber Society. Retrieved 2010-02-28.</ref>
