'''Marica Malović-Đukić''' ({{lang-sr-cyr|Марица Маловић-Ђукић}}; born 1949) is a [[List of Serbian historians|Serbian historian]], specialized in the economic and social history of maritime communes in the Middle Ages, with special focus on Kotor and Dubrovnik.{{sfn|Историјски институт Београд}} She finished studying history at the Faculty of Philosophy in Belgrade in 1973, with the work ''Длугошев списак српских градова'' for which she received the [[October Award (Belgrade)|October Award]] of the city of Belgrade.{{sfn|Историјски институт Београд}} She magistered with the work ''Стефан Дечански'' in 1977, and the doctorate dissertation ''Котор у XIII и XIV вијеку'' was defended in 1988.{{sfn|Историјски институт Београд}} She worked at the Historical Institute of SR Montenegro in Podgorica from 1975, and from 1988 she works at the Historical Institute of Serbia.{{sfn|Историјски институт Београд}} She has worked with the [[Serbian Academy of Sciences and Arts]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Naučni skup o Dušanovom zakoniku u SANU|date=19 March 2009|publisher=RTV|url=http://www.rtv.rs/sr_lat/nauka-i-tehnologija/naucni-skup-o-dusanovom-zakoniku-u-sanu_117178.html}}</ref> Her languages also include Italian, English, Latin and Old Slavic.{{sfn|Историјски институт Београд}}

